      "name": "CPB hemolysis applicability domain — Class II centrifugal pumps",
      "description": "The CFD model is applicable to Class II centrifugal blood pumps operating under CPB conditions with blood viscosity modelled as a non-Newtonian shear-thinning fluid (Carreau-Yasuda parameters within ±10% of reference values). The model is scoped to adult patients (haematocrit 35–45%), pump speeds 1500–3500 RPM, and flow rates 2–7 L/min. Extrapolation beyond these bounds, or to paediatric or ECMO applications, requires re-assessment."
