        "description": "RANS equations with SST k-ω turbulence closure selected based on documented literature precedent for centrifugal blood pump CFD. Haemolysis modelled via Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law applied to Lagrangian particle tracks. Acceptance criterion: model form selection justified by ≥2 peer-reviewed publications demonstrating applicability to centrifugal blood pump haemolysis prediction, with documented limitations acknowledged."
      },
      "rationale": "RANS-SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on demonstrated performance in centrifugal blood pump CFD: Bludszuweit (1995), Giersiepen et al. (1990), and the FDA critical path CFD round-robin (Hariharan et al. 2011) all support this closure for impeller-dominated flows at Re ~ 10⁵. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law (α=3.62×10⁻⁷, β=2.416, γ=0.785) is the most widely validated haemolysis model for comparative device assessment per ASTM F1841. Limitations (turbulent stress contribution to haemolysis, non-Newtonian effects on turbulence) are documented in the VV plan. Model form selection justified and documented; criteria met."
